by ogizanagi at 2016-01-18T22:43:30Z

Just for the record, I tried a pure CSS implementation, maybe you can give it a try to enhance it:

```diff
--- a/Resources/views/css/easyadmin.css.twig
+++ b/Resources/views/css/easyadmin.css.twig
@@ -349,8 +349,8 @@ a.btn-secondary:active {
 .easyadmin-vich-image img {
     border: 3px solid {{ colors.white }};
     box-shadow: 0 0 3px {{ colors.gray }};
-    max-height: 300px;
-    max-width: 400px;
+    max-height: 160px;
+    max-width: 250px;
 }
 .easyadmin-vich-file input[type="file"] {
     padding-top: 7px;
@@ -361,6 +361,33 @@ a.btn-secondary:active {
     display: none;
 }

+.easyadmin-vich-image a {
+    transition: all 0.3s;
+}
+.easyadmin-vich-image a img {
+    transition: all 0.2s;
+}
+.easyadmin-vich-image a:hover {
+    position: fixed;
+    z-index: 9999;
+    left: 0;
+    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.75);
+    width: 100%;
+    height: 100%;
+    bottom: 0;
+    opacity: 1;
+}
+.easyadmin-vich-image a:hover img {
+    position: absolute;
+    left: 0;
+    top: 0;
+    right: 0;
+    bottom: 0;
+    margin: auto;
+    max-height: 100%;
+    max-width: 100%;
+}
+
```

But I fear it might be more annoying than useful as it is.
It can be enhanced to respond on click instead on hover by using the `:target` pseudo-class & a predefined modal element. (See references below)

The js plugin mentioned by @reypm looks good. I don't know if there is lighter.

[Here](http://drublic.github.io/css-modal/) is also a full implementation of a pure CSS modal we can eventually inspire of. And some references:

- http://www.webdesignerdepot.com/2012/10/creating-a-modal-window-with-html5-and-css3/
- http://codepen.io/maccadb7/pen/nbHEg

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by Pierstoval at 2016-01-19T08:34:33Z

You could use `:active` instead of `hover` or `target`, this would be much better for UX (with a `cursor: pointer;` of course).

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by Pierstoval at 2016-01-19T08:38:52Z

Here's a really simple fiddle:

http://jsfiddle.net/8c7Vn/192/

```css
img {
    transition: max-width 0.25s ease;
    max-width: 250px;
    max-height: 150px;
    cursor: zoom-in;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: block;
}

img:active {
    max-width: 100%;
    max-height: 100%;
    cursor: zoom-out;
}
```

